<p><b>Mervyn Edward "Merv" Griffin, Jr.</b> (July 6, 1925 – August 12, 2007) was an American <a href="Television_host" title="Television host" class="mw-redirect">television host</a>, musician, actor, and <a href="Media_mogul" title="Media mogul" class="mw-redirect">media mogul</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-CNN_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CNN-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> He began his career as a radio and big band singer who went on to appear in film and on <a href="Broadway_theatre" title="Broadway theatre">Broadway</a>. From 1965 to 1986 Griffin hosted his own <a href="Talk_show" title="Talk show">talk show</a>, <i><a href="The_Merv_Griffin_Show" title="The Merv Griffin Show">The Merv Griffin Show</a></i>, produced by <a href="Westinghouse_Broadcasting" title="Westinghouse Broadcasting">Westinghouse Broadcasting</a> (also known as Group W). He also created the <a href="Game_show" title="Game show">game shows</a> <i><a href="Jeopardy!" title="Jeopardy!">Jeopardy!</a></i>, <i><a href="../Wheel_of_Fortune_(U.S._game_show)" title="Wheel of Fortune (U.S. game show)">Wheel of Fortune</a></i>, <i><a href="Click_(game_show)" title="Click (game show)">Click</a></i>, and <i><a href="Merv_Griffin's_Crosswords" title="Merv Griffin's Crosswords">Merv Griffin's Crosswords</a></i> with his own television production companies, <a href="Merv_Griffin_Enterprises" title="Merv Griffin Enterprises">Merv Griffin Enterprises</a> and <a href="Merv_Griffin_Entertainment" title="Merv Griffin Entertainment">Merv Griffin Entertainment</a>. During his lifetime, Griffin was considered an <a href="Entertainment_industry" title="Entertainment industry" class="mw-redirect">entertainment</a> <a href="Business_magnate" title="Business magnate">business magnate</a>.</p>
